#Task 1: Fork and Clone the Repository
Ok, so today's task is very simple 

✅ Step 1: Fork the Repository
1. Go to the GitHub repository you want to fork.

2. In the upper-right corner of the repository page, click the “Fork” button.

3. Choose your GitHub account as the destination (or organization if needed).

4. Now you have your own copy of the repository under your GitHub account.

✅ Step 2: Clone the Forked Repository
1. Go to your forked repository (e.g. https://github.com/Rohini-996/90DaysOfDevOps.git).

2. Click the “Code” button.

3. Copy the URL under HTTPS, SSH, or GitHub CLI.
